This an example of a reusable barrier class for multi-threaded programming. 
It includes it's own Doxygen code which can be compiled andon a HTML form. The Doxygen can be compiled in terminal and ran also in terminal.
It can also be ran with it's index file which is in the HTML folder within the Doxygen file. 
This program can be excuted using the makefile provided in the folder. This uses the g++ compiler and has features that allow you to delete
all of the object files or use the GDB debugger. 
